dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Countywide 30-cm Bare Earth DEM (m) for Bayfield County, WI 2022
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived 30-cm Digital Elevation Model (DEM) for Bayfield County, Wisconsin in 2022. This dataset has elevation values in meters and is in the WTM coordinate system: EPSG 3071. A DEM represents the bare-Earth surface, removing all natural and built features
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Administration - Geographic Information Office
uw_supplemental_s: This lidar data dataset was created by the WisconsinView Partners (WVP) – the WI Department of Administration’s Geographic Information Office in collaboration with the UW-Madison WisconsinView repository. Original lidar data in tiled format from federal or local lidar projects were used to create countywide mosaics of datasets such as DEMS, Intensity images, and DSMs in various projections and coordinate systems. For detailed metadata please visit: https://web.s3.wisc.edu/wsco-wisconsinview/lidar/Bayfield/Bayfield_2022_3DEP_Delivery/Metadata/Metadata.zip
